16 2021-05-24 loss of taste 16yoF patient came to our Moderna Mass Vax clinic on 4/26/21, inadvertently received COVID-19 vacci... Read more
Close
16yoF patient came to our Moderna Mass Vax clinic on 4/26/21, inadvertently received COVID-19 vaccine Moderna lot 007C21A ext 10/12/21. EUA for moderna is for age over 18. Patient reported later that patient had fever, HA, loss of taste, weight loss, increase in liver enzymes. Patient went to ED on 5/14/21 and came back again on 5/21/21, getting admitted to Ped unit x2days. She was diagnosed with infectious mononucleosis hepatitis, unlikely related to vaccine admin as per Dr., Ped ID specialist**. Patient became afebrile, LFT improved (ALT 577> 126, AST 349>74), condition stable and discharged on 5/23/21. Dr. follows up with the patient at his OP clinic.

Patients menstrual cycle started the day she received the moderna vaccine, the next day,02/13/2021, she stated it was heavier than she had ever had. Patient reported changing birth control 1-2 months previously. On 02/16/2021 Patient's father reported she was standing in the kitchen and her pupils were huge. Patient told parents she couldn't see or hear. Patient became unconscious for approximately 3 seconds. took patient to ER. ER was unable to find a cause. Loss of vision and hearing lasted approximately 3-5 minutes.
17 2021-03-03 oropharyngeal discomfort Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes ... Read more
Close
Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes to 1 hour after receiving her second Moderna vaccination on 2/24/21. She reported that she was told by her employer that the symptoms were due to the Moderna vaccine. She reportedly developed fever and some throat discomfort as well. Symptoms became persistent and disrupted sleep and was unable to work. She sought medical attention in the ER for persistent symptoms on 2/26/21. Extensive workup was essentially normal. She received Zofran, Decadron, IVFs, and Albuterol inhaler while in the ER. She reported improvement in her chest tightness and SOB after Albuterol. She was discharged home with instructions to f/u with her PCP in a couple of days for recheck.

I feel like something is crawling under my skin and the vaccine is extremely affecting my nervous system. I did not have this problem before I had the vaccine. It has not gone away and it is now April 23rd I still feel weak, not the same as I used to feel before having the vaccine, and my muscles are twitching all over my body. My face is twitching and my eye and there is nothing I can do to make it stop. I am so young and I thought the vaccine was safe but I am suffering from it. Especially in my feet I feel like they are tingling and vibrating and my calves are convulsing too. Meanwhile, my heart is fluttering and I feel like it is very hard for me to focus and I feel things crawling under my skin in my brain. The muscle convulsions are happening everywhere.

Pain and soreness in vaccination arm was immediate for the rest of the day. Started feeling achey and feverish at the end of the day towards nighttime and bedtime. Took a Tylenol before going to bed. Woke up at 6:00a.m. feeling achey and feverish again, more severe this time. Attempted to walk to get another Tylenol and take my temperature, vision blurred and was extremely cold, immediate nausea, felt like I was going to pass out. Shaking and chills. After drinking Gatorade, ginger ale and water and eating peanut butter toast, nausea settled. After a bit, experienced severe stomach cramps. Drank more ginger ale and Gatorade and took a Tylenol to relieve pain. After 30-45 minutes, pain relieved and I was able to go back to bed. Rest of the day experienced pounding headache and feverish and achey body. Experienced fever highest at 99.8 during the day. After 24 hours passed, feel 100% better and all symptoms and side effects relieved. Only thing sustaining is a little bit of pain and soreness in the arm.

18 2021-04-04 eye twitching Right eye twinching; lightheadedness; rash on hands; Nausea; DOB; This case was received via an unkn... Read more
Close
Right eye twinching; lightheadedness; rash on hands; Nausea; DOB; This case was received via an unknown source (no reference has been entered for a health authority or license partner) on 10-Feb-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 11-Feb-2021. This spontaneous case was reported by a nurse (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness), RASH (rash on hands), NAUSEA (Nausea) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) in an 18-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 037K20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. Concurrent medical conditions included Penicillin allergy since January 2021. On 29-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 29-Jan-2021, the patient experienced BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), RASH (rash on hands) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), NAUSEA (Nausea) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). At the time of the report, BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness), RASH (rash on hands), NAUSEA (Nausea) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Treatment for the events include 0.5ml Epinephrine on the left thigh This case concerns an 18 Y/O F hospitalized with serious unexpected events of blepharospasm, dizziness, rash, nausea, dyspnea. Event outcomes unknown. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Reporter did not allow further contact; Sender's Comments: This case concerns an 18 Y/O F hospitalized with serious unexpected events of blepharospasm, dizziness, rash, nausea, dyspnea. Event outcomes unknown. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

18 2021-04-19 oropharyngeal discomfort, tongue discomfort Patient came in for her first dose of Moderna vaccine today. I was called by MA to see Patient as ... Read more
Close
Patient came in for her first dose of Moderna vaccine today. I was called by MA to see Patient as Patient was having symptom(s) 15 minutes after the vaccine was given. I saw Patient at 0935. Patient stated that she feels pressure in her anterior throat, that it was hard for her to swallow saliva, and that her tongue felt big. I performed physical examination: Cardiovascular: RRR S1 S2 Pulmonary: Lungs clear to auscultation Mouth/Throat: Posterior pharynx doesn't look swollen, tongue doesn't look swollen MA and myself continued to monitor Patient. I asked Patient to call her mother who Patient stated was waiting downstairs. I asked MA to obtain vitals: BP: 128/79 HR: 102 bpm I explained to Patient and mother that I think Patient should be given the Epi-pen in order to prevent any of the symptom(s) from worsening. Patient and mother agreed to have the Epi-pen administered. At 0950, Patient stated that her tongue doesn't feel big anymore, but that she still feels pressure in her anterior throat. Patient asked for water, she was given a water bottle by MA. After drinking water, Patient stated it was hard to swallow the water. At 0955, I administered the Epi-pen in Patient's right thigh. Patient felt okay with the administration of the Epi-pen. I asked MA to observe Patient for 15 minutes, Mom was in the room with the Patient as well. At 1015, I went in to see Patient, and per MA and Patient, Patient was feeling much better. Patient stated that her symptom(s) had resolved, she was not feeling pressure in her anterior throat any longer, she was able to drink water normally, and she didn't feel that her tongue felt big any longer. I performed repeat physical examination: Cardiovascular: RRR S1 S2 Pulmonary: Lungs clear to auscultation Mouth/Throat: Posterior pharynx didn't look swollen, tongue didn't look swollen I asked MA to obtain repeat vitals: BP: 116/73 HR 94 bpm I have advised Patient to talk to her PCP about whether she should get the second dose of Moderna, or perhaps get another vaccine such as Pfizer in place of the second dose of Moderna. I have let Patient know that I will CC her chart to her PCP and will try to get a Telemedicine visit with the doctor for Patient during the next week. I have let Patient know that I will e-prescribe Epi-pen for her. I have advised Patient and Mom that if symptom(s) worsen or if new symptom(s) start (such as chest pain, SOB, hives, throat/mouth/face/tongue swelling or any other concerning symptoms) to take Patient to the ED. Mom and Patient understood and agreed.
18 2021-04-19 visual impairment, ringing in ears The 12:20 pm appointment today (4/20/21) had an adverse reaction to the IMZ. Patient was done receiv... Read more
Close
The 12:20 pm appointment today (4/20/21) had an adverse reaction to the IMZ. Patient was done receiving the vaccine at about 12:30 pm and I stated she would have to wait until 12:45 pm. Around 12:38 pm I noticed she looked a little pale and went to her side to check on her. The patient stated she was feeling light-headed, dizzy, nauseous, and had trouble with her vision. I had the patient lay down and elevate her feet. The technician also grabbed an ice pack to place behind her neck. Asked if she would like water. The patient then stated she was having trouble breathing/short of breath and her ears were ringing. Once the patient stated issues with breathing 911 was called. A code white had been called and management was in the pharmacy. The 911 operator continued to ask questions about the patient's status and stated to not give any water or medications. I continued to assess the patient's symptoms. Her vision improved; however, she continued to feel light-headed, nauseous, and having trouble breathing. A member of EMS was in the store and came over to assess the patient. He had the patient sit up but she continued to have the same symptoms. He assessed her IMZ site. She was not feeling itchy and had not developed any hives. The ambulance arrived. EMS evaluated the patient and then took her out of the store on the stretcher.

19 2021-04-29 sensitivity to light, visual impairment, light flashes or floaters in the eye, eye floaters About roughly two weeks after receiving this vaccine I had a migraine. I had never had a migraine be... Read more
Close
About roughly two weeks after receiving this vaccine I had a migraine. I had never had a migraine before so I went to urgent care, where they told me it would probably go away in a couple of days. It didn't, and I was having a whole horde of visual symptoms (floaters, flashing lights, photophobia, visual aura) so I went to Mass Eye and Ear ER about a week later. They did an examination of my eyes and told me it was all okay, and most likely due to a migraine. I assumed it would go away once more, but never did, with the symptoms continuing to become more frequent/severe. While the actual migraine part (head hurting to specify) would come and go, my visual symptoms never subsided. And despite MEE saying my vision was actually 20/15, so I could still objectively see fine, it was just not normal. I started to have vertigo, and more visual auras (a plain green line in my vision for a couple of minutes), and with these symptoms going on for about two weeks at this point, I went to an urgent care appointment at MGH, through my doctor. They administered some migraine medication (sumatriptan and zofran), but my visual symptoms did not improve. I was then sent to MGH er. They tested me for a whole myriad of things, as well as administering an MRI/MRA of the brain, and MRI of the spine, as well as performing a spinal tap, none of which yielded any significant findings. Many of my visual symptoms still persist, and the headache part, as well as vertigo, comes and goes. It has been almost a month since receiving the first dose and I am waiting to see if symptoms improve with the second. While it is obviously unclear as to whether this happened due to the vaccine or due to a third unknown factor, considering these symptoms developed roughly around the time you allegedly start to gain a significant immunity to COVID, and that no medical professionals have been able to find a clear reason for them, I feel as though it is possible and likely. (Also, I had previously had COVID, testing positive Jan 18th 2021, if that's of any relevance).

Close
Normal side effects: headache, chills, body aches/stiffness, joint pain, sore injection arm, fatigue Side effects had slow onset after shot was given. However, I took Tylenol (650mg) preemptively because of my experience with the first dose. This may have affected onset time and severity. Side effects had set in by 9 PM that evening, with the worst being the headache. Ringing in my ears (tinnitus) came with the onset of other side effects, and the severity coincided with the severity of the headache. I took Tylenol, which helped reduce (but not eliminate) side effects, but ringing in ears persisted, if only less intensely. I have continued to take Tylenol (and occasionally Ibuprofen--I tend to avoid because of stomach sensitivity), with all symptoms lessening over the week (5/3-5/10), except for ringing in ears and slight headache. The ringing does not seem to go away with OTC meds (Tylenol, Ibuprofen). It is worse in the left ear, which is the side I got the shot in.

Severe headache lasting more than two weeks. After 3 days I went to the emergency room. I went due to a number of symptoms(fever, chills, nausea, severe body aches, neck stiffness, blurred vision) the headache was my chief complaint and thought to be the cause of the other issues. My heart rate upon arrival was 223 causing me to be hooked up to a cardiac monitor, and my blood pressure was 72/56. I was swabbed for the flu and Covid. Both resulted negative. All labs blood and urine were normal. X-ray or chest was done and showed all clear. CT scan was also done and to my knowledge was clear. I was told I needed to get a lumbar puncture to check for meningitis because it was the only other thing they could think of. Upon doing the lumbar puncture CSF gushed from the needle used to puncture and my headache was gone within minutes. I was diagnosed with pseudotumor cerebri. Thought to be caused by my IUD. After going to see my OBGYN I was informed that my COVID vaccine had caused my IUD to release and unusual amount of hormones and that?s what caused the excess buildup of spinal fluid in my brain. I?m still, almost two months later experiencing headaches and back/neck pain. My IUD is still not working properly and is scheduled to be removed temporarily.

Friday, March 12th, 2021 at 11am I had a severe anaphylactic reaction to the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. My throat began to swell and became very short of breath. My chest was tight and felt as if it was being crushed. A nurse walked by me and noticed me grabbing my chest and immediately put me on a gurney. They took my mask off and discovered my lips were swelling and turned blue. My vitals were taken and was was given epinephrine in my left thigh. EMS was called and on board was given an IV Benadryl and steroids. Once at the hospital I was given Ativan, Pepsid and more Benadryl. I was discharged around 4pm and was back at the ED 3/13/21 early morning when I woke up with not being able to breathe, my throat swelling and crushing feeling in my chest. I was given more Benadryl and fluids, and was released 8am. 3/16/21 I came back to the ED as advised by a triage nurse on the phone, as I was having trouble breathing and the same crushing feeling in my chest.

She did not show any signs of redness, rash, or swelling. After sitting for a few minutes, and before EMS arrived, the patient said she was improving. She did not lose consciousness anymore but she still had a headache, nausea, and blurry vision. When EMS arrived they recommended that she get checked out at the emergency room, but the patient refused stating that she did not want to go to the hospital and that she was feeling better. The patient called her parents and they came and picked her up.

Patient is a 25 year old female. She presented to the clinic for her second dose of Moderna LOT #003C21A. According to patient's husband she has no significant past medical history but has ?passed out? with vaccines. No reaction noted with her first COVID vaccine. Approximately 10 minutes after receiving her injection today she told her husband that she wasn?t feeling well. She said was light headed and nauseated. Patient then proceeded to become nonresponsive. Her eyes deviated upward and her whole body became stiff. Her skin had notable pallor. She was lowered to the ground by staff, myself, and her husband, and put in a supine position with her legs elevated. 911 was called. This episode lasted approximately 40-60 seconds when she became responsive and cried out for husband. Her muscles relaxed and she became notably upset. She kept saying she wasn?t able to see or feel her extremities. Her lack of vision resolved within 10-15 seconds. She had weakness in her arms and legs but was able to squeeze her hands on command. She was alert and oriented X3. BP was 130/90. The patient was stable when the ambulance arrived to transport her to Hospital.
